                "RISK AND COMPLIANCE MANAGER\nIvanhoe Mines\nSandton, Gauteng\nPermanent\n \nAPPLY\n \nClosing Date 18 December 2023\n \nJob Details\nDivision: Ivanhoe Mines SA\nMinimum experience: Mid-Senior\nCompany primary industry: Mining and Metals\nJob functional area: Finance\n \nJob Description\nIVANHOE MINES is looking for a Risk and Compliance Manager \n\nIvanhoe Mines is a leading Canadian mining company committed to becoming a global leader in the supply of critical resources required to transition our world to a low-carbon, renewable future.  Ivanhoe is focused on developing and expanding its four principal mining and exploration projects in Southern Africa. The development of the Kamoa-Kakula copper mining complex in the Democratic Republic of Congo(DRC), the Platreef palladium-rhodium-platinum-nickel-copper-gold discovery in South Africa, the extensive redevelopment and upgrading of the historic Kipushi zinc-copper-germanium-silver mine, also in the Democratic Republic of Congo and exploration on the Western Foreland, near Kamoa-Kakula.\n \nPlay your part in our team succeeding...\nBy having to advise and adopt in a risk-based approach, to ensure that the material compliance risks implemented on the group are addressed and properly reduced.\n \nRequirements:\nCA (SA), MBA or Law Degree with at least,\n5+ years\u2019 experience in a compliance role position in a medium to large multinational firm with operations in South Africa, Africa and abroad.\nMust come from a mining, construction, or similar industry experience.\n\n\n\nYour Key Performance Activities will include but not limited to: \n\nProcess: \nDevelop and implement a compliance risk management process in line with generally accepted compliance practice.\nImplement a compliance monitoring programmes to identify and improve areas of compliance weakness and to ensure that there are adequate controls in place.\nDesign and implement a regulatory universe and monitor and update when required.\nEnsure that regulatory compliance in the Group gets the necessary attention it needs.\nDevelop a Group compliance framework which aligns to the Group risk management framework.\nDesign and lead a strong compliance culture in the business by effectively communicating to relevant stakeholders.\nConduct or direct the internal investigation of compliance issues.\nVerify that all regulatory policies and procedures have been documented, implemented, and communicated.\nProvide compliance assurance to the relevant management teams, group risk management committee, audit committee or social, ethics and risk committee\n \nThe finer details:\nWhen applying, please submit a PDF version of your CV together with certified copies (certification within a 3-month period) of your ID/passport, drivers licence and qualifications. \nShould you not hear from us within 30 days of the closing date please consider your application unsuccessful.\n \nAPPLY",
                "SAGE REPORTING SPECIALIST\nIvanhoe Mines\nSandton, Gauteng\nPermanent\n \nAPPLY\n \nClosing Date 30 November 2023\n \nJob Details\nDivision: Ivanhoe Mines SA\nMinimum experience: Associate\nCompany primary industry: Mining and Metals\nJob functional area: Finance\n \nJob Description\nIVANHOE MINES is looking for a Sage Reporting Specialist \n\nIvanhoe Mines is a leading Canadian mining company committed to becoming a global leader in the supply of critical resources required to transition our world to a low-carbon, renewable future.  Ivanhoe is focused on developing and expanding its four principal mining and exploration projects in Southern Africa. The development of the Kamoa-Kakula copper mining complex in the Democratic Republic of Congo(DRC), the Platreef palladium-rhodium-platinum-nickel-copper-gold discovery in South Africa, the extensive redevelopment and upgrading of the historic Kipushi zinc-copper-germanium-silver mine, also in the Democratic Republic of Congo and exploration on the Western Foreland, near Kamoa-Kakula.\n \nPlay your part in our team succeeding...\nTo provide report related support and maintenance for all end-users for the Sage 300 People system. Assist in the analysis, testing and modifications of current and newly developed systems reports. Execute on new implementations, integrations and optimisation to provide system reporting services to all the companies within the group.  \n \nYou will have the following:\nBCom Degree or Diploma\n3-5 years in a Sage/Systems reporting environment with Payroll and HR experience \nExperience in African countries highly advantageous \nExperience in the mining environment highly advantageous \nWriting and consolidating of reports (mainly excel reporting) \n \nYou will have advanced skills and knowledge in:\nSage People 300 report writing experience \nSQL  report writing experience \nKnowledge of Payroll and HR policies and procedures with regards to reports \nSystem database construction understanding \nAll-round understanding of information systems\n \nPersonal Competencies should include:\nStrong verbal and written communication skills \nPatience to provide technical support \nInterpersonal skills \nAttention to detail and analytical skills \nOrganizing and planning skills\nProfessionalism \nTrustworthy (Confidentiality of payroll and HR information) \nTechnological affinity \n \nYour Key Performance Activities will include but not limited to:\nSage 300 People Report development \nAdminister Reporting within the Sage 300 system \nEstablish and maintain relationships across functional areas to enable collaboration and knowledge sharing across the business. \nAdhere to reporting best practice for areas of responsibility \n \n \nThe finer details:\nWhen applying, please submit a PDF version of your CV together with certified copies (certification within a 3-month period) of your ID/passport, drivers licence and qualifications. Office based position.\n\n \nShould you not hear from us within 30 days of the closing date please consider your application unsuccessful. \n \nAPPLY",
                "SAGE SPECIALIST I\nIvanhoe Mines\nSandton, Gauteng\nPermanent\n \nAPPLY\n \nClosing Date 30 November 2023\n \nJob Details\nDivision: Ivanhoe Mines SA\nMinimum experience: Associate\nCompany primary industry: Mining and Metals\nJob functional area: Other\n \nJob Description\nIVANHOE MINES is looking for a Sage Specialist I \n\n\nIvanhoe Mines is a leading Canadian mining company committed to becoming a global leader in the supply of critical resources required to transition our world to a low-carbon, renewable future.  Ivanhoe is focused on developing and expanding its four principal mining and exploration projects in Southern Africa. The development of the Kamoa-Kakula copper mining complex in the Democratic Republic of Congo(DRC), the Platreef palladium-rhodium-platinum-nickel-copper-gold discovery in South Africa, the extensive redevelopment and upgrading of the historic Kipushi zinc-copper-germanium-silver mine, also in the Democratic Republic of Congo and exploration on the Western Foreland, near Kamoa-Kakula.\n \nPlay your part in our team succeeding...\nTo provide support and maintenance for all end-users for the Sage 300 People system. Assist in the analysis, testing and modifications of the system.\nExecute on new implementations, integrations and optimization's to provide system support services to all the companies within the group. The duties include  database management, customizations and maintenance of the different modules. \n \nYou will have the following:\nBCom Degree or Diploma\n3 - 5 Years in a Sage/Systems Administration environment with Payroll and HR system supervisory experience.\nExperience in African countries highly advantageous.\nExperience in the mining environment highly advantageous\n \nYou will have advanced skills and knowledge in:\nSage People 300 experience\nKnowledge of Payroll and HR policies and procedures\nSystem database construction understanding\nAll-round understanding of information systems\n \nPersonal Competencies should include:\nStrong verbal and written communication skills\nPatience to provide technical support \ninterpersonal skills\nAttention to detail \nOrganizing and planning skills\nProfessionalism \nTrustworthy (Confidentiality of payroll and HR information) \nTechnological affinity \n \nYour Key Performance Activities will include but not limited to: \nSage 300 People implementation and system support \nAdminister the Sage 300 system \nEstablish and maintain relationships across functional areas to enable collaboration and knowledge sharing across the business \nAdhere to reporting best practice for areas of responsibility \n \nThe finer details:\nWhen applying, please submit a PDF version of your CV together with certified copies (certification within a 3-month period) of your ID/passport, drivers licence and qualifications. Office based position.\n \nShould you not hear from us within 30 days of the closing date please consider your application unsuccessful. \n \nAPPLY"
