                " \n \n \n \n \nOPERATIONS ENGINEER\nRustenburg\n \nPURPOSE OF THE JOB: To ensure safety, health of employees (legally responsible as a 2.13.3.1.) and ensure efficient equipment operation and availability.\n \nMINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS AND REQUIREMENTS:\nB Engineering/BSc Engineering/National Diploma is essential\nGovernment Certificate of Competency Mines and Works in Electrical or Mechanical Engineering is essential (2.13.3.1)\n2 - 4 years operational experience within Mining/ Plant is essential\nRegistration as a professional certificated engineer would be an advantage.\n2 year recognised junior engineering program training is essential.\n2 to 3 years Project Management experience would be desirable.\nValid Medical Certificate or medically fit in order to obtain such a certificate.\n  \n \nCOMPETNCIES:\nApplied knowledge of general management methodologies and principles would be advantageous.\nMust have Legal & Operational knowledge related to the Mining industry.\nApplied knowledge of strategic management principles would be advantageous.\nComputer Literacy (MS Office, MS Project, SAP R/3) is essential.\nTime management and negotiation skills are advantageous.\nData analysis and Presentation skills are essential.\nMentoring and coaching skills are advantageous.\nPreventative maintenance skills are essential.\n \nKEY PERFORMANCE AREAS\nTo ensure zero harm to employees and the environment by meeting legal and SHEQ regulations/ compliance.\nTo ensure that equipment is well maintained and efficiently managed, i.e., equipment availability is good to ensure that production targets are met.\nTo ensure effective project delivery to enable future growth and reach production targets.\nTo implement effective financial management processes.\nTo ensure effective people management methodologies, inclusive of people development (subordinates vary between 200 400).\nTo apply engineering expertise, conduct effective design checks/ apply appropriate specifications on equipment (quality & safety key criteria)\n \n\nIMPORTANT: Short listed candidates may be subjected to a psychometric assessment. Preference will be given to candidates from the designated groups in line with the provisions of the Employment Equity Act, the Companys Recruitment Policy and Employment Equity Plan.\n\n \nPOPIA Disclaimer: By sending your CV to the e-mail address on this advertisement you agree to:\nThe processing of your personal information and sharing it with third parties for verifications.\nThe exercising of your rights provided for by POPIA.\nTo acknowledge that Impala will keep the record of your personal information confidential.\n \nAPPLY FOR POSITION",
                "MANAGER: TECHNICAL SERVICES\nRustenburg\n \nPURPOSE OF THE JOB:  \nTo ensure effective co-ordination of the Technical Services departments at Shaft level for Rustenburg operations. To ensure that key customers are supported for service delivery (technical information and guidance).\n \nMINIMUMQUALIFICATIONS AND REQUIREMENTS:\nHons. Degree or equivalent in Mineral Resources e.g. mining, geology etc. is essential.\nOther relevant certificate of competency for Technical Services, Mineral Resources or Mining is essential.\nProfessional registration in field of expertise is essential.\nFinancial qualification would be advantageous.\n10 years Technical/Mineral Resource experience in tabular ore bodies, preferably within the platinum mining industry is essential.\nManagerial experience of mine technical services function, e.g., Geology, Survey, Mine Planners, Rock Engineering, Engineering, Safety and Ventilation is desirable.\n  \nCOMPETNCIES:\nKnowledge of Impala standards and practices\nMineral resource and technical management principles and processes knowledge\nMineral resource and technical systems (IT) knowledge\nTechnical evaluation (analytical) skills\nPresentation skills\nGeneral computer/IT knowledge\nGood verbal and written communication skills\nMine planning software knowledge and Mine planning skills\n \nKEY PERFORMANCE AREAS:\nTo ensure effective functioning and good integration between the various technical departments on the shaft or within a shaft cluster.\nTo co-ordinate all short, medium to long term planning as well as optimisation work at shaft level.\nTo ensure all operational planning is effective (G-sheets, pre-planning, lost blast analysis etc.).\nTo provide technical advice to the Mine Manager and General Manager.\nTo monitor operational achievement and provide advice to the Mine Manager and General Manager on deviations and impacts (volumes, quality of mining, cost and revenue).\nTo ensure all technical reporting is provided as required on and off the shaft.\nTo act as liaison between MRM Manager Operations and the technical heads as required.\nTo ensure that the service provided to mining by the technical services team is effective.\nTo co-ordinate all ad hoc requests of information at shaft level, and to ensure application of relevant standards and practices within the Mine Technical Services department.\n \nIMPORTANT: Short listed candidates may be subjected to a psychometric assessment. Preference will be given to candidates from the designated groups in line with the provisions of the Employment Equity Act, the Companys Recruitment Policy and Employment Equity Plan.\n \nPOPIA Disclaimer: By sending your CV to the e-mail address on this advertisement you agree to:\nThe processing of your personal information and sharing it with third parties for verifications.\nThe exercising of your rights provided for by POPIA.\nTo acknowledge that Impala will keep the record of your personal information confidential.\n \nAPPLY FOR POSITION"
