                " \n \nSECTION PRODUCTION GEOLOGIST\nLocation:  GT, ZA\nCompany:  Gold Fields Group Services (Pty) Ltd\nJob Req ID: \nFarm Modderfontein, Old Vereeniging Road, Westonaria, 1779\nPO Box 57, Westonaria, 1780, South Africa\nTel +27 11 411 1000 - Dir +27 11 411 1797 - Fax +27 11 411 1588 \nwww.goldfields.com\nSouth Deep is recruiting!\n \nThis is an opportunity to bring your expertise to a dynamic and engaged team of professionals, working together to become the beacon of pride for our people, our communities, our stakeholders, and our shareholders.\n \nAt South Deep, we value each person\u2019s individual and collective contribution and support your ongoing development, helping you to achieve your career and our business aspirations.\n \nPOSITION: Senior Production Geologist     \nJOB GRADING: D-Lower       \nDEPARTMENT: Technical Services            \nSITE: South Deep Gold Mine\n \nThe Senior Production Geologist is accountable for delivering on-mine production geology function support including the design, execution and monitoring of the South Deep integrated operational geology strategy and programme incorporating Exploration and Production Geology.  Drawing off an established mine geology track record, the incumbent is responsible for the technical evaluation and optimisation of existing and new geological methodologies, techniques, and technologies to drive efficient operational delivery of mapping, drilling, sampling, logging, grade control and ore flow reconciliation as well as all associated QA/QC functions.   As a Senior Production Geologist, the successful incumbent assumes responsibility for embedding a values-based culture of safety, productivity, and respectful engagement in all aspects of operational delivery.\n \nMinimum Requirements\nPostgraduate qualification in Geosciences or Mineral Resource Management Discipline e.g. BSc (Hons) Geology, BSc (Hons) Geosciences etc.\nAt least 10 years\u2019 experience in operational Geology / Mineral Resources Management\nProven track record in mine production geology, underground mapping, geological modelling, orebody evaluation, sampling/assaying and mine-to-mill reconciliation\nEstablished QA/QC capability across the geology value-chain\nProven proficiency in applying relevant geological modelling software (Datamine/Leapfrog etc.).\nExperience in developing and maintaining spatial geological and structural models\nProven track record in participating and leading project(s) and/ or operational reviews\nDemonstrated ability to apply a systematic, knowledge-based problem-solving and structured methodologies to investigate risks and opportunities that will lead to effective, value-add technical solutions and process optimisation\nBe declared medically fit for the position and environment, as determined by a risk-based medical examination at the Gold Fields Occupational Health Centre and pass a Heat Tolerance Screening test, and such other tests as may be required to assess the applicant\u2019s suitability for employment\n \nKey Competencies:\nAdvanced operational safety leadership experience with demonstrated safety delivery record\nDemonstrated experience in leading and working with diverse teams and achieving sustained high performance.\nExcellent written and spoken communication and stakeholder management skills\nUnderstanding of mining geology Mineral Resource development as well as Research and Development\nKnowledge of best practice across the different processes withing the geology function\n \nDuties and Responsibilities:\nParticipate in and contribute towards the formulation and execution of the mine\u2019s various safety, health, environment and risk management campaigns\nLead work teams in the execution of all technical programmes, including mapping, sampling, drilling, grade control, and reconciliation processes\nEmbed and maintain standardized geological practices for mine geology, geological modelling, exploration drilling, ore sampling/assaying and mine-to-mill reconciliation\nContinuously evaluate and optimise resource delineation and grade control programmes and, implement remediation interventions as required\nMaintain up to date spatial geological data such as structural block models while maintaining systems to optimise exploration delivery, diamond drilling, resource modelling and estimation\nImprove awareness of and input into technical risk evaluation at site for geosciences and development of processes and action plans to mitigate such risks\nEnsure that geoscientific data and documents are appropriately managed throughout the geology value chain and that the most updated and complete version is stored in the appropriate storage location\nParticipate / lead regular and ad hoc short, medium and long-term operational planning and scheduling sessions with a focus on actively identifying and collaboratively solving operational delivery challenges\nLead the coordination of geological support to the Mining and Metallurgy departments while ensuring optimal data-driven analysis to enable detailed mine planning, scheduling and ore characterization and extraction\nContribute towards compilation and publication of Annual Resource Statement in ensuring alignment with relevant mineral reporting codes and standards such as SAMREC, JORC, ROPOs, etc\nConduct appropriate research on emerging geological leading practice to identify potential methodologies, techniques and technologies to optimise application, improve efficiency and geological confidence at South Deep\nEffective contract management resulting in excellent safety and planned productivities\n \n \nClosing Date: 30 November 2023\n                            \nPlease note that the Gold Fields code of conduct strictly prohibits the exchange of any payment as part of its recruitment process.\n \n Should you require any assistance or have any challenges in applying for a position, please contact the Recruitment hub on 011 411 1387\n \nGold Fields is committed to the achievement and maintenance of diversity and equity in employment\n \nNOTE: all relevant certificates must be attached to your CV in order to be considered for shortlisting\n \n* South Deep Joint Venture is an unincorporated joint venture between GFI Joint Venture Holdings Proprietary Limited (Reg. No. 1998/023354/07) and Gold Fields Operations Limited (Reg. No. 1959/003209/06), both wholly-owned subsidiaries of Newshelf 899 Proprietary Limited (Reg. No. 2007/019941/07) a subsidiary of Gold Fields Limited (Reg. No. 1968/004880/06).\n \nGold Fields Operations Limited Directors: M Preece (Chairman), R Bardien, NA Chohan, P Matete, BL Mokoatle\nGFI Joint Venture Holdings Proprietary Limited Directors: M Preece (Chairman), R Bardien, NA Chohan, P Matete, BL Mokoatle\nCompany Secretary: Gold Fields Group Services (Proprietary) Ltd\n \nAPPLY NOW \u00bb\n \n \n \n ",
                " \n \n \n \nTRACKLESS DIESEL MECHANIC\nLocation:  \nGT, ZA\nCompany:  Gold Fields Group Services (Pty) Ltd\nJob Req ID: \nFarm Modderfontein, Old Vereeniging Road, Westonaria, 1779\nPO Box 57, Westonaria, 1780, South Africa\nTel +27 11 411 1000 - Dir +27 11 411 1797 - Fax +27 11 411 1588\n www.goldfields.com\n \nSouth Deep is recruiting!\n \nThis is an opportunity to bring your expertise to a dynamic and engaged team of professionals, working together to become the beacon of pride for our people, our communities, our stakeholders, and our shareholders.\n \nAt South Deep, we value each person\u2019s individual and collective contribution and support your ongoing development, helping you to achieve your career and our business aspirations.\n \nPOSITION: Trackless Diesel Mechanic\nJOB GRADING: C-Lower\nDEPARTMENT: Engineering\nSITE: South Deep Gold Mine\n \nThe Trackless Diesel Mechanic will be responsible for the Refurbishment/Assembling/Commissioning of Equipment and maintain Reliability on the Equipment until hander over to the Relevant Section for production.  The role requires safe task execution in respect of Changing of Major Components, troubleshooting breakdowns, performing preventative maintenance, and repairing faults.  Team members are expected to demonstrate a focus on safety, achievement, and team engagement in all aspects of their work\n \nMinimum Requirements:\nGrade 12 or equivalent\nRecognized Diesel Mechanic/Millwright/Fitter Trade Certificate\nHave 5 years\u2019 experience in a mechanized mining environment as a Diesel Mechanic/Millwright/Fitter\nProven working knowledge of Trackless Machines. Sandvik/Epiroc/Aard/Caterpillar\nBe declared medically fit for the position and environment, as determined by a risk-based medical examination at the Gold Fields Occupational Health Centre and pass a Heat Tolerance Screening test, and such other tests as may be required to assess the applicant\u2019s suitability for employment\n \nKey Competencies:\nGood communication and interpersonal skills\nBe able to interpret hydraulic drawings and use with fault-finding\nExtensive experience on Trackless Equipment/Component\nProven track record of production achievements\nPrepared to work overtime/irregular hours and perform standby duties as required\nComputer literacy with basic MS Office proficiency\n \nDuties and Responsibilities:\nEnsure health and safety of self and team members by applying relevant standards and procedure\nPerform inspections in accordance with the Mine Health and Safety Act regulations, manufacturing, and Company standards\nResponsible for the maintenance of applicable standards and conditions within assigned areas of responsibility\nResponsible for the safe and proper installation and repairs of equipment aligned to scheduled planned refurbishments and maintenance, breakdown management and ad hoc assignments\nAccountable for the complete delivery of daily task assignments and, reporting of outstanding or work to be scheduled in accordance with established preventative and breakdown maintenance standards\nCarry out RCA to eliminate repeat failures and implement remedial actions\nCollaborate with operational teams to ensure preparation and release of units for planned breakdown and ad hoc maintenance tasks\nCollaborate with team and planned maintenance teams to ensure optimal preparation, spares, etc. ahead of tasks being assigned and executed\nEngage in further training and related activities to ensure continuous refinement of own skills and competencies\n \n \nClosing Date: 22 November 2023\n                            \nPlease note that the Gold Fields code of conduct strictly prohibits the exchange of any payment as part of its recruitment process.\n \n Should you require any assistance or have any challenges in applying for a position, please contact the Recruitment hub on 011 411 1387\n \nGold Fields is committed to the achievement and maintenance of diversity and equity in employment\n \nNOTE: all relevant certificates must be attached to your CV in order to be considered for shortlisting\n \n* South Deep Joint Venture is an unincorporated joint venture between GFI Joint Venture Holdings Proprietary Limited (Reg. No. 1998/023354/07) and Gold Fields Operations Limited (Reg. No. 1959/003209/06), both wholly-owned subsidiaries of Newshelf 899 Proprietary Limited (Reg. No. 2007/019941/07) a subsidiary of Gold Fields Limited (Reg. No. 1968/004880/06).\n \nGold Fields Operations Limited Directors: M Preece (Chairman), R Bardien, NA Chohan, P Matete, BL Mokoatle\nGFI Joint Venture Holdings Proprietary Limited Directors: M Preece (Chairman), R Bardien, NA Chohan, P Matete, BL Mokoatle\nCompany Secretary: Gold Fields Group Services (Proprietary) Ltd\n \nAPPLY NOW \u00bb\n \n \n \n \n ",
                "TRACKLESS CREW LEADER\nLocation: GT, ZA\nCompany:  Gold Fields Group Services (Pty) Ltd\nJob Req ID: \nFarm Modderfontein, Old Vereeniging Road, Westonaria, 1779\nPO Box 57, Westonaria, 1780, South Africa\nTel +27 11 411 1000 - Dir +27 11 411 1797 - Fax +27 11 411 1588 \nwww.goldfields.com\n \nSouth Deep is recruiting!\n \nThis is an opportunity to bring your expertise to a dynamic and engaged team of professionals, working together to become the beacon of pride for our people, our communities, our stakeholders, and our shareholders.\n\n \nAt South Deep, we value each person\u2019s individual and collective contribution and support your ongoing development, helping you to achieve your career and our business aspirations.\n \nPOSITION: Trackless Crew Leader (Miner)\nJOB GRADING: C2\nDEPARTMENT: Mining\nSITE: South Deep Gold Mine\n \nThe Trackless Crew Leader is accountable for executing the safe and efficient delivery of assigned monthly production plan, leading operational teams to achieve prescribed safely goals and ensuring quality delivery according to operational standards.\n \nMinimum Requirements:\nMatriculated or Equivalent with a recognized Blasting Certificate\nAt least 5 years\u2019 production experience in a deep level trackless mine with relevant TM3 equipment/machinery certificates\nSound working knowledge of relevant Mine Health & Safety legislation\nSecure full Gold Fields Security and Related Occupational Screening\nBe declared medically fit for the position and environment, as determined by a risk-based medical examination at the Gold Fields Occupational Health Centre and pass a Heat Tolerance\n \nKey Competencies:\nAdvanced safety leadership capability with proven safety campaign delivery record\nAccomplished team and people leader\nStrong inter and intra-team collaboration skills\nAdvanced practical mining experience with sound appreciation for full mining operational value chain\nSound spoken and written English communication skills\nAbility to cope with ambiguity with high personal resilience and change adaptability\nEstablished problem-solving skills\n \nDuties and Responsibilities:\nProviding and maintaining a safe environment with minimum risk to the health and safety of the crew\nEnsuring compliance to the Mines Health & Safety Act and related operational safety standards\nAccurate and timeous reporting of all relevant safety and production matters\nPromoting and developing team effectiveness within the department\nEnsuring that all relevant production targets are met continuously\nTaking accountability for proper discipline in the section\nEnsuring effective availability and utilization of equipment and materials\nEnsuring control of explosives and that planning and budget is controlled and applied correctly\n \nClosing Date: 24 November 2023\n                            \nPlease note that the Gold Fields code of conduct strictly prohibits the exchange of any payment as part of its recruitment process.\n \n Should you require any assistance or have any challenges in applying for a position, please contact the Recruitment hub on 011 411 1387\n \nGold Fields is committed to the achievement and maintenance of diversity and equity in employment\n \nNOTE: all relevant certificates must be attached to your CV in order to be considered for shortlisting\n \n* South Deep Joint Venture is an unincorporated joint venture between GFI Joint Venture Holdings Proprietary Limited (Reg. No. 1998/023354/07) and Gold Fields Operations Limited (Reg. No. 1959/003209/06), both wholly-owned subsidiaries of Newshelf 899 Proprietary Limited (Reg. No. 2007/019941/07) a subsidiary of Gold Fields Limited (Reg. No. 1968/004880/06).\n \nGold Fields Operations Limited Directors: M Preece (Chairman), R Bardien, NA Chohan, P Matete, BL Mokoatle\nGFI Joint Venture Holdings Proprietary Limited Directors: M Preece (Chairman), R Bardien, NA Chohan, P Matete, BL Mokoatle\nCompany Secretary: Gold Fields Group Services (Proprietary) Ltd\n \nAPPLY NOW \u00bb",
                "DRIVER FORKLIFT UG\nLocation:   GT, ZA\nCompany:  Gold Fields Group Services (Pty) Ltd\nJob Req ID: \nFarm Modderfontein, Old Vereeniging Road, Westonaria, 1779\nPO Box 57, Westonaria, 1780, South Africa\nTel +27 11 411 1000 - Dir +27 11 411 1797 - Fax +27 11 411 1588 \nwww.goldfields.com\n \nSouth Deep is recruiting!\n \nThis is an opportunity to bring your expertise to a dynamic and engaged team of professionals, working together to become the beacon of pride for our people, our communities, our stakeholders, and our shareholders.\n \nAt South Deep, we value each person\u2019s individual and collective contribution and support your ongoing development, helping you to achieve your career and our business aspirations.\n \nPOSITION: Driver Forklift\nJOB GRADING: BL\nDEPARTMENT: Engineering\nSITE: South Deep Gold Mine\n \nThe forklift operator is responsible for the safe and effective transport of material cars to and from the shaft in accordance with standard operating procedures.\n \nMinimum Requirements:\nGrade 12 or equivalent\nForklift driver license\nValid driver license\nAt least 2 years\u2019 experience as Forklift operator in a mining environment\nBe declared medically fit for the position and environment, as determined by a risk-based medical examination at the Gold Fields Occupational Health Centre and pass a Heat Tolerance Screening test, and such other tests as may be required to assess the applicant\u2019s suitability for employment\n \nKey Competencies:\nEstablished personal safety delivery record\nStrong inter and intra-team collaboration skills \nSound spoken and written English communication skills\nCompletion of a machine appreciation awareness programme (O4R/M4R or equivalent)\nAbility to cope with ambiguity with high personal resilience and change adaptability\nEstablished problem-solving skills\n \nDuties and Responsibilities:\nMaintains Safety, Health and Environmental practices according to standards and procedures\nDoes a pre-use inspection on this equipment by means of a checklist and report deficiencies to supervisor\nPerforms basic maintenance on equipment e.g. top up engine oil, water and hydraulic oil, check for oil leaks and clean equipment according to standards and procedures\nPerforms end of shift procedures according to standards and procedures e.g., parks the forklift at the designated area, cleans equipment and reports to supervisor\nPerforms any other activities necessary for the effective completion of his/her work\nOperates the forklift to safely transport material cars to and from the Shaft in accordance with standard operating procedures\nAssessing weight of loads to be lifted\nAdhering to Surface Traffic Management plan as set out by the mine standard\nSafe operation of a Forklift\n \n \nClosing Date: 22 November 2023\n                            \nPlease note that the Gold Fields code of conduct strictly prohibits the exchange of any payment as part of its recruitment process.\n \n Should you require any assistance or have any challenges in applying for a position, please contact the Recruitment hub on 011 411 1387\n \nGold Fields is committed to the achievement and maintenance of diversity and equity in employment\n \nNOTE: all relevant certificates must be attached to your CV in order to be considered for shortlisting\n \n* South Deep Joint Venture is an unincorporated joint venture between GFI Joint Venture Holdings Proprietary Limited (Reg. No. 1998/023354/07) and Gold Fields Operations Limited (Reg. No. 1959/003209/06), both wholly-owned subsidiaries of Newshelf 899 Proprietary Limited (Reg. No. 2007/019941/07) a subsidiary of Gold Fields Limited (Reg. No. 1968/004880/06).\n \nGold Fields Operations Limited Directors: M Preece (Chairman), R Bardien, NA Chohan, P Matete, BL Mokoatle\nGFI Joint Venture Holdings Proprietary Limited Directors: M Preece (Chairman), R Bardien, NA Chohan, P Matete, BL Mokoatle\nCompany Secretary: Gold Fields Group Services (Proprietary) Ltd\n \nAPPLY NOW \u00bb"
