                " \n \nRE-ADVERTISED: CUSTOMER EXPERIENCE (CX) DEVELOPER (MBSA)\nJob category: Marketing / Vertrieb / Kommunikation\nDepartment: Customer Experience\nOrganization: Mercedes-Benz South Africa Ltd\nLocation: Pretoria, ZA\nStart date: Immediately\nPublication date: 13.11.2023\nJob number: MER0002X62\n \nTasks\nObjective of the job:\n\u00b7Development and Reporting role in Mercedes-Benz Marketing & Sales.\n\u00b7 To be the technical custodian of MBSA\u2019s marketing applications.\n\u00b7 Planning, aspects of design, development, implementation, testing, maintenance and support.\n\u00b7Understand and optimise data flow within MB security guidelines & data privacy laws.\n\u00b7Ensure a focus on data-driven marketing & sales, automation and innovation\n \nMain Tasks:\nReporting and Dashboards:\n\u00b7Monitor, maintain and update databases accurately on relevant systems in collaboration with IT.\n\u00b7Ensure that all required reports are drafted, developed, tested, approved and distributed to relevant stakeholders accurately, within the agreed timeframe, on the right platforms, securely.\n\u00b7Be able to apply logic (rules, algorithms) to analyse data and provide reports & insights where required.\n \nQualifications\nRelevant graduate qualification and/or experience including qualifications in the disciplines relating to information technology, web development or data science.   \n \nContact\nMercedes-Benz South Africa Ltd\nMBSA Place, 210 Aramist Place\n0181 Pretoria\nMmalekoba Amanda Msomi\nE-Mail: amanda.Msomi@mercedes-benz.com\n \nJOIN US\n \n \n \n ",
                " \n \n \n \nBUSINESS ANALYST (GENERAL) X 1\nJob category: IT / Telekommunikation\nDepartment: Hub-Production & Global Logistics (In- & Outbound)\nOrganization: Mercedes-Benz South Africa Ltd\nLocation: Mercedes-Benz Manufacturing South Africa Ltd, East London\nStart date: Immediately\nPublication date: 09.11.2023\nJob number: MER0002X25\n \nTasks\nJob Description\nTo improve efficiency, reduce waste, identify and implement solutions, meet project deadlines and accurately document the necessary requirements to be done in accordance with local / global strategic planning and standards in compliance to the Company's Integrity & Anti Bribery Codes, Conflict of Interest Policy & S.H.E.Q requirements and to perform delegated S.H.E.Q tasks and duties & to inform superior about deviations\n \nThe Job Requirements\n      Demonstrated ability to foster an environment for ideation, prototyping and production\n      Demonstrated business acumen to take from design to implementation and preferably experience scaling a concept\n      Must have IT Development and Systems Knowledge\n      Experience with software development methodologies and practices (Agile, Scrum, etc.)\n      Experience in Data Analysis and Advanced Proficiency in Microsoft Office suite, including Word, Excel, and Outlook\n      Strong Leadership Behaviours with good People Management skills and Problem Solving Skills\n \nQualifications\n      Minimum NQF 7 \u2013 BSC/BCom/BTech in Information Technology or B. Eng. (Industrial Engineering) or relevant equivalent\n \nKnowledge and Experience\n      Minimum of 2 years\u2019 experience in IT, or at least 6 months participation on our MBSA Graduate Development Programme\nEmail for queries: ithubvacancies@mercedes-benz.com\n\n \nThank you for your interest in the MBSA IT HUB. Kindly note that we do not accept any email applications, this email address is for queries only, Please register on our careers website site and apply for suitable IT vacancies; Careers home page | Mercedes-Benz Group > Careers (https://group.mercedes-benz.com/careers/)  \n \nClosing date: 30 November 2023\n \nContact\nMercedes-Benz South Africa Ltd\n7 Settlers Way Gately Industrial Township\n5200 East London\nDetails to location\nJanis Caron Page-Wood\nE-Mail: janis.page-wood@mercedes-benz.com\n \nJOIN US\n \n \n \n ",
