                " \n \nSTUDENTS\nYou will be responsible for detailed planning of all training activities\nYou will be responsible for completion of documentation and verification of training documentation \nYou will be responsible for people movement that is correctly and timeously done.\nManagement of training rotation plan.\nLaunch training support\nEquipment management\n \nQualifications:\nNational Diploma / l BSc / B Tech Industrial / Mechanical / Electrical Eng.\nMicrosoft suite knowledge, particularly Excel\nCommunication and Analytical skills\nProblem Solving skills\n \nStudents\nLegal entity:\nBMW (South Africa) (Pty) Ltd.\nLocation: South Africa\nJob field: Assembly\nJob ID: 230003DZ\nPublication date: 16.11.2023\n \nAPPLY",
                "MAINTENANCE PLANNER\n \nScope of responsibility\nProject planning and realization of measures to maintain or improve equipment or system performance (repairs, continuous improvements/ optimizations, & new installations, etc.). Includes multiple conveyor technologies, monitoring/information systems, and all process equipment in the technology. Design and development of maintenance process, equipment, and systems. Manages maintenance key performance indicators for the department. Generates proposals for technical specifications, request for quotations, and SLA (Service level agreements). Determines root cause for equipment/system performance gaps and the optimum solutions regarding costs, quality, ergonomics, technical innovation, and environment. Planning of maintenance measures (repairs, maintenance, fault recertification, alterations, optimizations, component detachments, etc.) from identification through realization to improve equipment reliability and performance. Delivery and/or updates of Preventative Maintenance plans, documentation (electronic and hard copy), and spare parts including min/max levels. Development measures and concepts for the further development and stabilization of existing maintenance processes. Ensures all assigned projects are on schedule and at or under approved budget (Assembly variance to budget). Collaborates with internal and external process partners and suppliers. Performs other duties as assigned by management. \n \nResponsibility of the function\nTo ensure the successful and timeous completion of all PM\u2019s required to ensure maximum availability and runtime for the production equipment.\nResponsible to ensure spares are returned to the stores as to ensure availability in the maintenance storeroom.\nCreate and maintain an accurate equipment register in accordance with the plant wide standard and the specific requirements of the department concerned.   \nTo ensure that spares, consumables, and tools required to perform maintenance are available when needed.\nTo create and maintain a preventative maintenance program for equipment considering the requirements of the OHS Act, the ISO 9001 and 14001, OSHAS 18001 series of standards, product standards as well as what is economically and practically viable.\nAccountable and responsible for Planning, Control, Organising and leading Maintenance Activities.  Establish required team, set objectives, task timing, evaluate SHE aspects and controlling of overhead budget.\nTo assign maintenance work in the most economical way possible, accurately record necessary information and adhere to the work order procedure.\nTo administrate and manage the working hours of all the maintenance personnel in your area of responsibility.\nTo assist superior in compiling necessary maintenance reports and to present results when necessary.\nEnsure continuous improvement of quality on maintenance tasks and plant availability.\nMaintenance project support.  For example, the development of new procedures or systems to improve the utilization of maintenance resources and the PM process.\nShutdown planning particularly from a maintenance perspective.\nSupplier development. From time to time it will be necessary to identify new suppliers for maintenance spares or develop new suppliers to obtain the most cost-effective components.\nGeneral projects from other disciplines. From time to time a planner may be required as a form of personal development or due to resource constraints to take on projects outside of the maintenance discipline.\nTo support Company and Departmental objectives.\nTo support and enforce the team building concept.\nChecks that safety standards are met\nOrganizational development\nPlans, investigates, and optimizes the introduction of new production methods.\nTests new consumable materials as well as production materials, and documents results. Establish contacts and Liaise with BMW AG and suppliers for continuous improvement and constant reviews.\nAccountable and responsible for liaising with financial controllers on buying and budgeting of storeroom spares.\nMaintain and oversee all Occupational Health, Safety and Environmental issues and give constant feedback to maintenance manager and maintenance engineer.\nEnsure that all legal requirements pertaining to maintenance are strictly adhered to, i.e. people development, training, and machinery safety.\n \nKey accountabilities of the function\n\n\nMaintenance project support.  For example, the development of new procedures or systems to improve the utilization of maintenance resources and the PM process.\nShutdown planning particularly from a maintenance perspective.\nSupplier development. From time to time it will be necessary to identify new suppliers for maintenance spares or develop new suppliers to obtain the most cost-effective components.\nGeneral projects from other disciplines. From time to time a planner may be required as a form of personal development or due to resource constraints to take on projects outside of the maintenance discipline.\nTo support Company and Departmental objectives.\nTo support and enforce the team building concept.\nChecks that safety standards are met\nOrganizational development\nPlans, investigates, and optimizes the introduction of new production methods.\nTests new consumable materials as well as production materials, and documents results. Establish contacts and Liaise with BMW AG and suppliers for continuous improvement and constant reviews.\nAccountable and responsible for liaising with financial controllers on buying and budgeting of storeroom spares.\nMaintain and oversee all Occupational Health, Safety and Environmental issues and give constant feedback to maintenance manager and maintenance engineer.\nEnsure that all legal requirements pertaining to maintenance are strictly adhered to, i.e. people development, training, and machinery safety.\n \nQualifications and Experience\n National Engineering Diploma \u2013 N6(Mechanical or Electrical)\nThe equivalent of 5+ years of professional experience in a manufacturing role or maintenance technician role or maintenance planning role.\n \nWork Experience\n\u00b7         5+ years of experience in manufacturing environment (automotive preferred).\n\u00b7         5+ years maintenance experience (preventive maintenance practices, shutdown/start-up management, mechanical/electrical).\n\u00b7         5+ years problem solving, data analysis, and continuous improvement.\n\u00b7         SAP Maintenance Planning and Processing\no    Creation of Maintenance plans\no    Creation of new MS parts\no    BOM\no    Function Hierarchy\n \nAdditional Skills\n\u00b7        Ability to work in team, assertiveness, and good communication skills.\n\u00b7         Liaise with external and internal partners.\n\u00b7         Initiative of his own.\n\u00b7         Mobility and flexibility. Ability to work in team, assertiveness, and good communication.\n\n\u00b7         Problem solving (use of Ishikawa, 5-Why, 1-5-20, etc.)\n\u00b7         Thorough knowledge of BMW quality standards\n\u00b7         Communication skills, positive attitude, and approach\n\u00b7         Computer literacy (MS Word, MS Excel, MS PowerPoint, MS Outlook, SAP)\n\u00b7         Material Control and Supply\n\u00b7         Knowledge in Engineering Changes\n\u00b7         P\u00dc Processes\n\u00b7         DS&R Processes \n\u00b7         Cross cultural tolerance and experience with dealing at all levels in the organization structure\n\u00b7         People Management skills\n \nMAINTENANCE PLANNER\nLegal entity: BMW (South Africa) (Pty) Ltd.\nLocation: South Africa\nJob field: Equipment Maintenance\nJob ID: 2300039D\nPublication date: 15.11.2023\n \nAPPLY",
                "MANAGER: CORPORATE, DIRECT AND SPECIAL SALES.\n \nThe main purpose of the function is to ensure that the manager steers the department to maximize sales through the different channels. The manager is also required to ensure that enough support is provided to the department to grow the business by steering sales and marketing activities to drive sales. This function is also required to successfully steer the business relationship between Direct Sales, NSC Finance and Financial Services. The role is also required to actively manage the corporate annual budget and ensure that spend is tracked according to the budget plan and Cost of Retail. In terms of sales the role is also required to support the sales targets by actively seeking to close deals with customers when required in support of the team in terms of achieving the annual sales targets and Cost of Retail measures. The role is also responsible to ensure full compliance when dealing with customers which includes pricing, contracting, invoicing, and retailing.\nDefines and implements short-term and long-term development corporate strategy to achieve profitable volume contribution to BMW, MINI and Motorrad.\nResponsible for proposing and agreeing with customers the annual forecast upfront where possible.\nEnsure pricing from a risk and lease perspective is covered and planned for the quarter to ensure the best possible planning.\nSteer sales through the different channels to achieve the annual targets.\nDevelops the retailer network and the sales channel (online platforms etc).\nDesign\u2019s monetary incentive schemes for the different corporate sales channels. Ensures payment takes place in a precise and on time method to ensure a smooth relationship.    \nLiaise with IT regularly to ensure that processes are enhanced on a regular basis.  \nCoordinates overall sales and marketing planning for the different channels within the direct sales area.  \nFacilitate marketing activities which includes events for the direct customers.\nDevelop and maintain relationships with all stakeholders in NSC and SF to ensure smooth running of the business.\nDevelop and maintain relationships with all departments as well as team members to ensure that all job requirements are completed to their highest potential.\nSteers the planning of direct and retailer business (processes, communication, and policy guidelines) in the market with various departments in NSC based on past performance and market trends.\nPromotes cross-functional interaction within NSC on sales related topics. \nSets targets and develops measures in conjunction with relevant process partners for the department.\nResponsible for escalating risk and compliant topics identified within the department and other respective areas.\nSteer improvement projects as well as Compliance processes within the direct sales process.\nSteers guidelines and training plans for processes and policies to suit ZA\u2019s market conditions and best practices.\nInitiates solutions for conflicting demands of sales volume targets, profitability targets, dealer profitability, sales, and customer expectations in terms of product substance and price for BMW premium positioning requirements.\nDeals with increased complexity and breadth of BMW/MINI and Motorrad model portfolio and technological innovation and increasing use of online/remote channels to sell to customers.\nEnsure that all support is given to redefine and grow the direct channel and ensure that proper assessment of the marketplace is made and that where possible the department can act swiftly to develop an outstanding offering for the customer base relative to the competition.\nAdapts Corporate strategy and planning to rapidly changing market conditions including \u2018hyper-competition\u2019 and competitor downward re-positioning, which requires constant analysis and recommendations to secure the most optimum combination of sales volumes and profitability.\n \nQualifications:\nHonours / Degree in Business Management, Marketing, Engineering, or Finance. A Master\u2019s degree would be beneficial.\nManagerial experience of 4 years leading a high performing team (preferable within a multinational company).\nAt least 5 years of operational sales experience with a good understanding of the product knowledge and experience with dealing within a direct sales model.\nExperience in the automotive industry (sales, marketing) would be beneficial.\nIdeally experience in sales with an NSC is desirable. \nRetail/dealer experience/working knowledge required.\nLeading a channel or business unit of a large team would be an added advantage.\nGood working knowledge of MS Office suite, SAP\nHigh analytical skills and the ability to conclude large fleet deals to a small group of customers.\n \nMANAGER: CORPORATE, DIRECT AND SPECIAL SALES.\nLegal entity: BMW (South Africa) (Pty) Ltd.\nLocation: Midrand\nJob field: Corporate Sales\nJob ID: 230003P7\nPublication date: 09.11.2023\n \nAPPLY"
