                " \n \nSENIOR PRODUCT MANAGER\nLOCATION SOUTH AFRICA \u2013 JOHANNESBURG\nCATEGORY MARKETING\n \nABOUT ABBOTT\nAbbott is a global healthcare leader, creating breakthrough science to improve people\u2019s health. We\u2019re always looking towards the future, anticipating changes in medical science and technology.\n \n\nAt Abbott, you can do work that matters, grow, and learn, care for yourself and family, be your true self and live a full life. You will have access to:\n \n\nThis position works at Johannesburg location in the Established Pharmaceuticals Division that we are committed to bringing the benefits of our trusted medicines to more people in the world\u2019s fastest-growing countries. Our broad portfolio of high-quality and differentiated branded generic medicines reaches across multiple therapeutic areas including gastroenterology, women's health, cardiometabolic, pain management/central nervous system, and respiratory.\n \n\n\u2022 Responsible for development of brand plans, marketing and sales objectives, strategies, advertising and promotion and ensure successful execution thereof for EAC region\n\u2022 Evaluate the practicality and potential of new products and market development within EAC\n\u2022 Coordinate cross functional brand teams and management of agencies to implement plans\n\u2022 Accountable for the development of the EAC CLUSTER digital strategy and be appointed as the digital champion in this regard\n\u2022 Develop annual and monthly sales volume and profit forecasts, pricing and expense budgets.\n\u2022 Forecast product requirements, identify potential supply issues and develop contingency plans.\n\u2022 Oversee planning of Doctor Detail / Hospitals & Pharmacy sales promotion and advertising to drive performance of products within portfolio and determine to-market strategies and sales tactics to achieve sales objectives.\n\u2022 Ensure sales force adoption of key promotional activities through product and campaign training to sales force on a regular basis.\n\u2022 Review promotional budget, manage changes as required and communicate at proposed forecast stage.\n\u2022 Ensuring that the product and marketing efforts are aligned with company\u2019s overall strategy and goals.\n\u2022 Coordinating the formulation of sound marketing strategies for each promoted product in line with Marketing Excellence principles as well as portfolio and company financial and strategic objectives and ensure full implementation.\n\u2022 Demonstrated track record of successful development and implementation of insight-driven digital promotional campaigns and activities to drive demand\n\u2022 Drive and co-ordinate the roll out of regional driven digital campaigns within the cluster\n\u2022 Impact measurement through the creation of a dashboard for feedback to the leadership and regional team\n\u2022 Understanding financial and business considerations impacting both the company capabilities and readiness to support a strategic drive via new product and/or service introduction.\n\u2022 Developing and sustaining productive customer relationships.\n\u2022 Responsible for interactions with Third Parties / TPMs to ensure achievement of agreed upon objectives\n\u2022 Managing company resources consistent with company policies to achieve organizational goals.\n \n\n\u2022 Proven track record in the Pharmaceutical Industry, with a minimum 4 year product management experience.\n\u2022 Tertiary qualification in Health Sciences and/or Business Sciences or equivalent. Is essential.\n\u2022 Additional, Marketing qualification/IMM/Commercial qualification is an advantage\n\u2022 At least 3-5 Years Pharmaceutical sales experience with proven strong successful track record and sound organizational skills, financial acumen and ability to multi-task.\n\u2022 Proven product launch and brand planning experience.\n\n\u2022 Experience in managing effective channel and/or value chain management and experience in the pharmacy selling.\n\u2022 Preference: from generic background/ experience & MUST have handled multiple brands. Preference from Generic company background\n\u2022 Previous experience in establishing relationships, KOL development & maintenance for the key brands.\n\u2022 Strong leadership competencies including making difficult decisions, initiative, integrity and adaptability.\n\u2022 Strong interpersonal relations and customer focus.\n\u2022 Strong digital marketing & promotional skills \u2022 Strong ability to interpret sales & marketing figures + market / trend analysis.\n\u2022 Proven ability to influence cross-functional teams without formal authority.\n\u2022 Experience in working with market data / market analysis (IMS, Impact Rx, etc)\n\u2022 Energetic, self \u2013 starter and proven customer centric approach.\n\u2022 Excellent written and verbal communication skills.\n\u2022 Computer literacy: Excel, PowerPoint, is essential.\n \n\n \nFollow your career aspirations to Abbott for diverse opportunities with a company that can help you build your future and live your best life. Abbott is an Equal Opportunity Employer, committed to employee diversity.\n \nConnect with us at , on Facebook at  and on Twitter @AbbottNews and @AbbottGlobal.\n \n \n \n ",
