                " \n \nCHIEF ENGINEER\nListing reference: mr_001449\nListing status: Online\nApply by: 17 November 2023\n \nPosition summary\nIndustry: Mining & Quarrying\nJob category: Other: Mining\nLocation: Alldays\nContract: Permanent\nRemuneration: Market Related\n \nIntroduction\nMurray & Roberts Cementation invites suitably qualified candidates to apply for the position of Cheif Engineer to be placed in VenetiaMine, near Alldays Limpopo. The successful candidate will report to the Engineering Manager. The company will provide remuneration and benefits relevant and appropriate to the position. Preference will be given to Historically Disadvantaged South African (HDSA) candidates. Applications only open to South African Citizens / Permanent Residents.\n \nJob description\nThe successful candidate will be responsible for, but not be limited to:\n\u2022       Co-ordination of M&RC Site Engineer outputs\n\u2022       Effectively lead, motivate, coach and develop site engineering teams to achieve production and safety targets\n\u2022       Provide mechanical, electrical, structural and civil on site leadership and professional execution of construction work to designs, drawings, standards, specifications and legal regulations\n\u2022       Forecasts and plans are live and site engineering resources are in place in accordance with, but not limited to, project scope, budget, plans, scheduling and procurement\n\u2022       Drive rapid resolution of engineering issues, identify site technical risks, contribute to innovative solutions and enforce change management discipline\n\u2022       Maintenance of fleet and equipment to best industry benchmarks of cost effectiveness, availability and reliability\n\u2022       Maintain quality standards, integrity of reporting and communications\n\u2022       Required training, methods, documentation, risk assessments and procurement schedules are in place (Schedule integration, Engineering POP plan integration)\n\u2022       Effective engagement with site project team, the client\u2019s project team and manage/resolve interference when it affects engineering function productivity\n\u2022       Team and self-understand and comply with legal regulations and M&RC\u2019s policies, procedures, standards and safety protocols and ensure zero harm when carrying out work\n\u2022       Effective self and team management in alignment with M&RC\u2019s values and leadership initiatives\n\u2022       Proactive risk management of contract\n \nMinimum requirements\nSuitable candidates must possess the following minimum qualifications and skills:\n\u2022       BSc Engineering, BTech or National Higher Diploma Engineering from a recognised institution\n\u2022       DMR Government Certificate of Competency to practice as an Engineer (GCC Mines and Works - Mechanical or Electrical)\n\u2022       Project management qualification and ECSA registration (advantageous)\n\u2022       Proficient in MS Office including MS Projects\n\u2022       Valid Driver\u2019s license and Medically fit to work underground\n\u2022       Drawing and design reading and interpretation, skills Enablement and leadership skills\n\u2022       Project and change management skills\n\u2022       Ability to apply expertise and technology, deliver results and meet customer expectations\n\u2022       Reporting skills (progress, quality, planning and scheduling)\n\u2022       Excellent communication skills with ability to negotiate and resolve issues\n \nSuitable candidates must have the following work experience:\n\u2022       Minimum 10 years in a senior role, with hands on experience managing a large fleet (50 units) of TMMM, or opencast mining fleet and service/repair workshop.\n\u2022       Experience in vertical shaft operation and maintenance, including shaft sinking\n\u2022       Managed a fleet utilizing an enterprise fleet management system such as SAP, JDE, Karabo, Maximo, Pragma or similar\n\u2022       Operation and execution of a QA system and associated documentation\n\u2022       Application and execution of standards related to construction work, structures and structural integrity, quality controls, drafting procedures and conducting risk assessments\n \nAll appointments will be done in line with our employment equity strategy.\n \nDisclaimer\nThe Recruiter may amend, delete or expire jobs at any time without notification.\nMurray & Roberts reserves the right not to proceed with filling the position.\nAn application will not in itself entitle the applicant to an interview.\nIf you do not receive any feedback on your application within 4 weeks from the closing date, please consider your\n \nPLEASE APPLY HERE\n \n \n \n ",
                "PROJECT MANAGER\nListing reference: mr_001444\nListing status: Online\nApply by: 16 November 2023\n \nPosition summary\nIndustry: Mining & Quarrying\nJob category: Other: Mining\nLocation: Alldays\nContract: Permanent\nRemuneration: Market Related\n \nIntroduction\nMurray & Roberts Cementation invites suitably qualified candidates to apply for the position of Project Manager to be placed in Venetia Mine, near Alldays Limpopo The successful candidate will report to the Senior Project Manager. The company will provide remuneration and benefits relevant and appropriate to the position. Preference will be given to Historically Disadvantaged South African (HDSA) candidates. Applications only open to South African Citizens / Permanent Residents.\n \nJob description\nThe successful candidate will be responsible for, but not be limited to:\n\n\u00b7       Safe achievement of production and financial targets to client's and M&RC's standards\n\u00b7       Reception and delivery of employees / equipment / material to the underground operation\n\u00b7       Utilise strategic, management and technical skills to plan, delegate, control and monitor tasks through to project delivery in line with M&RC's project management framework\n\u00b7       Manage and schedule mining / construction activities to project scope, ensure team understands original scope Monitor and maintain critical path and project status on MS Projects\n\u00b7       Lead, develop and coach employees to ensure effective day to day operations in alignment with M&RC's values\n\u00b7       Identify talent, critical and core skills and implement talent management initiatives to ensure business continuity\n\u00b7       Build relationships cross functionally to ensure efficient delivery against common objectives\n\u00b7       Maintain and improve stakeholder and client relationships to ensure smooth workflows and timeous project delivery Enhance the effectiveness and efficiency of work practices and systems by optimizing all available resources, i.e. people, technology, finance and systems\n\u00b7       Identify, develop and implement controlled change initiatives to ensure project continuity\n\u00b7       Manage risk and operational discipline in line with legislation, policies, procedures and standards to ensure successful outcomes.\n\u00b7       Manage the project in line with contractual and commercial requirements, extension of time and claims formulation Follow up monthly on project certificates and valuations\n\u00b7       Self and team use SharePoint as a repository for project information and project management assurance \n \nMinimum requirements\nSuitable candidates must possess the following minimum qualifications and skills:\n\u00b7       Grade 12 or NQF Level 4 equivalent\n\u00b7       BSc / BEng / BTech in Mining or Engineering\n\u00b7       Mine Managers Certificate of Competency / Government Certificate of Competency [Engineering Mines & Works] Project Management Professional [Preferred]\n\u00b7       Business / Financial Management qualification [Advantageous]\n\u00b7       Proficient in Microsoft Office [Excel, Projects, Word & PowerPoint]\n\u00b7       Exposure to CCS [Construction Computer Software]\n\u00b7       Entrepreneurial and commercial thinking skills, with in-depth understanding of contracts & project financials Strategic thinking, enablement and leadership skills\n\u00b7       Sound analytical, logical reasoning, judgement and decision making skills\n\u00b7       Ability to apply expertise and technology, deliver results and meet customer expectations Excellent communication \n \nSuitable candidates must have the following work experience:\n\u00b7       Minimum 5 years of operational project management experience in an underground mining environment, with experience as a 2.6.1 legal appointee  \n\u00b7       Experienced in successfully managing industrial relations and union community engagement in a highly unionised environment\n\u00b7       Sound knowledge, understanding and experience of Trackless Mechanised Mining & Mine Development of large excavations.\n\u00b7       Sound knowledge, understanding and experience of single & multiple heading utilization and optimization.\n\u00b7       Sound knowledge, understanding and experience of TMM utilization and appreciation.\n\u00b7       Working knowledge of Project Management principles, frameworks, methodologies and system requirements, with proven depth of experience in project management i.e. meeting project deadlines, achieving financial targets and commercial entitlements \n \n \nAll appointments will be done in line with our employment equity strategy.\n \nDisclaimer\nThe Recruiter may amend, delete or expire jobs at any time without notification.\nMurray & Roberts reserves the right not to proceed with filling the position.\nAn application will not in itself entitle the applicant to an interview.\nIf you do not receive any feedback on your application within 4 weeks from the closing date, please consider your\n \nPLEASE APPLY HERE",
                "ARTISAN FITTER\nListing reference: mr_001445\nListing status: Online\nApply by: 16 November 2023\n \nPosition summary\nIndustry: Mining & Quarrying\nJob category: Other: Mining\nLocation: Musina\nContract: Permanent\nRemuneration: Market Related\n \nIntroduction\nMurray & Roberts Cementation invites suitably qualified candidates to apply for the position of Artisan Fitter to be placed in Limpopo, Musina. The successful candidate will report to the Foreman Engineering. The company will provide remuneration and benefits relevant and appropriate to the position. Preference will be given to Historically Disadvantaged South African (HDSA) candidates. Applications only open to South African Citizens / Permanent Residents.\n \nJob description\nThe successful candidate will be responsible for, but not be limited to:\nEngineering installations are constructed according to agreed standards, procedures and specifications.\nEngineering equipment is maintained according to agreed standards and schedules.\nEngineering equipment is repaired according to agreed standards and schedules.\nCompliance with SHEQ, M&RC and client standards, policies, procedures and safety protocols\nCost containment, high mean time to failure after repairs\nEffective stakeholder engagement\nCompetent, motivated, disciplined and positive team\nEffective self and team supervision in alignment with MRC values and leadership initiatives\n \nMinimum requirements\nSuitable candidates must possess the following minimum qualifications and skills:\nGrade 12\nSection 26 Fitter/Diesel Mechanic Trade Certificate / MIETTB Trade Certificate through a registered body\nValid Medical certificate of Fitness\nValid First Aid Certificate\nValid Code EB driver's license\nGood communication skills in English\nAble to solve problems within agreed standards, policies and procedures.\nTeam leadership and management skills\nSound listening communication skills.\nSelf-motivated self-starter with high levels of initiative\nAble to make decisions within agreed parameters.\nJob planning skills\nSuitable candidates must have the following work experience:\n5 year's mining industry experience (underground and surface)\n5 year's trade experience as a TMM Fitter\nAll appointments will be done in line with our employment equity strategy.\n \nDisclaimer\nThe Recruiter may amend, delete or expire jobs at any time without notification.\nMurray & Roberts reserves the right not to proceed with filling the position.\nAn application will not in itself entitle the applicant to an interview.\nIf you do not receive any feedback on your application within 4 weeks from the closing date, please consider your\n \nPLEASE APPLY HERE"
