                " \n \nCOMMERCIAL CHANNEL STRATEGY SENIOR MANAGER, AFRICA\nLocation: Johannesburg, Gauteng ZA\nJob ID: R-95711\nTime Type: Full time\nJob Type: Full-time\nRelocation: none\nPost Date: October 31, 2023\nShare This Job\nCommercial Channel Strategy Senior Manager, Africa\n \nAPPLY NOW\n \nOur vision is loved brands, done sustainably, for a better shared future. We strive to provide cutting-edge excellence in ingredients, innovation, design, and marketing.\n \nAbout the role\nThis role serves as the lead in the organization between the category/brand teams and commercial operating teams to communicate initiatives to bottlers and customer teams. The successful candidate should be able to demonstrate, relationship building and leadership capabilities while working across multiple channels.\n \nWhat You\u2019ll Do for Us \nResponsible for Commercial construct (based on Annual Business Plan, Channel strategy, PICOS guideline, shopper knowledge) into category strategy and campaigns for defined portfolio. Define where to play and how to win strategies and 360 campaign toolkits inputs, addressing shopper/channel needs across path to purchase.  Delivers via true integration into End-to-End process and collaboration across system.\nLeveraging commercial network inputs (Revenue Growth Management, Integrated Commercial Execution, Value to Market and Channel) for commercial integration (eg distribution / occasion / brand / package / price / channel strategy) into category strategy and plans.\nResponsible for the connection of category and channels, with occasion platforms approach.  Collaboration with Picture of Success and network to drive campaigns through to execution.\nAid Annual Business plan input on commercial strategy for the brands, leveraging Customer & Commercial Leadership network.\nRepresent channel input into Monthly Business review.\nBe the lens of the Channel in the categories assigned and represent Customer & Commercial Leadership functions in the category extended team. \nSupport commercial capabilities development within category, leveraging network as needed.\nTrack main indicators, review business performance, and design impactful actions to improve when results are below targets.\nContinuously share information, insights, and knowledge with KO System, developing platforms to materialize those insights into actions.  Integrate into teams, where category business problem.\nDefine value-added programs execution guidelines with the customer and commercial leadership areas to win in the market at the @ Point of Sale, based on Coca-Cola portfolio and Channel needs.\nCentral bottler office commercial engagement and alignment.\nCollaboration with Customer Value Creation into commercial sell in decks.\n \nQualifications & Requirements \n10+ years of leadership experience in Commercial, Shopper, RGM / Customer/Trade Strategy\nStrong business acumen with broad and deep understanding of consumers, shoppers and customers is mandatory with ability to bridge consumer/brand opportunities with customer relevance.\nStrong Analytical as well as integrating multiple data points into a compelling, actionable narrative\nDesirable to have candidates with Customer experience\nExceptionally strong leadership and influencing skills needed, across levels within internal and external organisation.\nThe role(s) requires ability to understand, analyse and connect what matters to our Consumers, Shoppers, Customers, as well as the competitive and industry dynamics, macro-economics and forecasts \u2013 all of which are required to build holistic and truly powerful propositions.\nThe Role covers multiple markets and is cross functional, working with markets and customer verticals and therefore requires strong interpersonal, leadership, project management and communication skills.\nCommunicating Effectively: Conveying information and ideas in a clear, meaningful and timely manner, providing information to ensure understanding and confidence\nDrives Innovative Business Improvements \u2013 Develops ideas and gains others\u2019 commitment. Seizes opportunities that can deliver the greatest value, promoting an innovative environment\nConnecting the dots, Data Analysis & Interpretation: Capability and judgement to identify, leverage and convert the right insights, from different data sources into holistic & compelling selling stories. \nNetwork: builds strong network to leverage and share knowledge and approaches\n \nWhat We Can Do For You \nIconic Brand: Work on the most recognized brand in the world and be part of developing the brands next chapter. \nExposure to World Class Leaders: Availability to global marketing leaders that will expand your network and exposure you to emerging digital platforms and marketing insights.  \nCreative Team Culture: Be inspired by the best brand leaders and agencies in the world, which creates a creative culture that supports taking risks and innovation. \n \nSkills:\nPromotional Strategies; Price Management; Strategic; Category Management; Competitor Analysis; Marketing Strategies; Microsoft Office; Communication; People Management; Teamwork; Finance Strategy; Collaboration; Financial Forecasting; Leadership; Media Planning; Trade Marketing; Marketing Campaigns; Key Performance Indicators (KPI); Integrated Marketing; Sales Analysis; Product Roadmapping; Channels Strategy; User Experience Analysis; Search Engine Optimization (SEO); Long Term Planning; Digital Marketing; Brand Management; Search Engine Marketing (SEM)\n\nOur Purpose and Growth Culture:\nWe are taking deliberate action to nurture an inclusive culture that is grounded in our company purpose, to refresh the world and make a difference. We act with a growth mindset, take an expansive approach to what\u2019s possible and believe in continuous learning to improve our business and ourselves. We focus on four key behaviours \u2013 curious, empowered, inclusive and agile \u2013 and value how we work as much as what we achieve. We believe that our culture is one of the reasons our company continues to thrive after 130+ years. Visit Our Purpose and Vision to learn more about these behaviours and how you can bring them to life in your next role at Coca-Cola.\nWe are an Equal Opportunity Employer and do not discriminate against any employee or applicant for employment because of race, colour, sex, age, national origin, religion, sexual orientation, gender identity and/or expression, status as a veteran, and basis of disability or any other federal, state or local protected class. When we collect your personal information as part of a job application or offer of employment, we do so in accordance with industry standards and best practices and in compliance with applicable privacy laws.\n \nAPPLY NOW\n \n \n \n ",
                " \n \n \n \nCONSULTANT - DATA GOVERNANCE & OPERATIONS\nLocation: Johannesburg, Gauteng ZA\nJob ID: R-95394\nTime Type: Full time\nJobType: Full-Time\nRelocation: none\nPost Date: October 30, 2023\nShare This Job\nConsultant \u2013 Data Governance & Operations\n \nAPPLY NOW\n \nPosition Title: Consultant, Data Governance & Operations\nPosition Location: Africa (Johannesburg)\n \nJob Description Summary \nThe Coca-Cola Company is seeking an exceptional talent to fill the Consultant, Data Governance & Operations role. It involves analyzing, documenting, and maintaining business processes, products, services, and technology. It emphasizes upholding high-quality data records in alignment with the company's data management strategy to improve business processes and technology. The individual in this role will ensure effective data utilization, sharing, and compliance with quality standards while collaborating with various teams and stakeholders. This is an individual contributor role.\n \nWhat You\u2019ll Do for Us\n\u00b7 Maintain and safeguard documentation on procedures and standards for data management and governance.\n\u00b7 Create and maintain Data records in accordance with the organization\u2019s process standards, data standards, policies and objectives. This includes enriching the Data with data from sources in- and outside the organization.\n\u00b7 Act as the contact point for the operating unit and partners for Data questions/requests\n\u00b7 Support the solving of data issues within the organizational systems, proactively and reactively.\n\u00b7 Support impact analyses for Data changes executed on organizational systems.\n\u00b7 Conduct Data Quality Assessment for the organization as needed\n\u00b7 Actively champions data management projects and initiatives.\n\u00b7 Help implement and maintain Data Quality and Data Governance metrics within the organization.\n\u00b7 Review metrics and monitor the data quality and raise concerns about Data quality, data governance and related issues as necessary to the data stewards and Data manager\n\n\u00b7 Ensure that Data requests are handled according to the Service Level Agreement (SLA), using the organization tooling\n \nQualifications & Requirements:\n\u00b7 Bachelor\u2019s Degree in a related field\n\u00b7 1+ years of experience in data management, governance and operations\n\u00b7 DAMA certification is a plus\n\u00b7 Working knowledge of Agile tools (e.g. JIRA, Azure DevOps,etc) and methodologies (Scrum, Kanban) is preferred\n\u00b7 CPG experience is a plus\n \nWhat We Can Do for You:\n\u00b7 Purpose Driven: Purpose driven approach that empowers our people to protect the environment and communities we serve while delivering safe & quality products.\n\u00b7 Global Connections: Allows you to develop, enhance and maintain global connections that allow us to move faster and learn from others.\n\u00b7 Community of Belonging: We\u2019re an organization that believes our ability to continually grow and build the right atmosphere where people feel safe and empowered, lets you bring your best self to work\n \nOur Purpose and Growth Culture:\nWe are taking deliberate action to nurture an inclusive culture that is grounded in our company purpose, to refresh the world and make a difference. We act with a growth mindset, take an expansive approach to what\u2019s possible and believe in continuous learning to improve our business and ourselves. We focus on four key behaviours \u2013 curious, empowered, inclusive and agile \u2013 and value how we work as much as what we achieve. We believe that our culture is one of the reasons our company continues to thrive after 130+ years. Visit Our Purpose and Vision to learn more about these behaviours and how you can bring them to life in your next role at Coca-Cola.\nWe are an Equal Opportunity Employer and do not discriminate against any employee or applicant for employment because of race, colon, sex, age, national origin, religion, sexual orientation, gender identity and/or expression, status as a veteran, and basis of disability or any other federal, state or local protected class. When we collect your personal information as part of a job application or offer of employment, we do so in accordance with industry standards and best practices and in compliance with applicable privacy laws.\n \nAPPLY NOW\n \n \n \n ",
                " \n \n \n \n \nMANAGER, GLOBAL MARKETING PROCUREMENT STUDIO X\nLocation: Johannesburg, Gauteng ZA\nAdditional Locations: Nairobi, Nairobi Area, KELagos, Lagos, NG\nJob ID: R-94129\nTime Type: Full time\nJob Type: Full-time\nRelocation: No\nPost Date: October 26, 2023\nShare This Job\nManager, Global Marketing Procurement Studio X\n \nAPPLY NOW\n \nLocation: Africa\nROLE LOCATION: The location of the positions and whether or not relocation benefits are provided will be discussed at the time of offer. In instances where relocation is provided, current mobility policies will apply. All policies are subject to amendment, revision, or discontinuance at the sole discretion of the Company.\nWe are changing the face of marketing procurement. The Coca-Cola marketing organisation is the best in the world and we are looking for a dynamic, connected manager to evolve the next chapter in how we approach our agency relationships. \nThe GMP Studio X Champion for The Coca-Cola Company (TCCC) will act as a part of the Global Marketing Procurement (GMP) Organisation working closely with the marketing organisations at global, category & Operating Unit (OU) levels, with PACS teams and FDS supporting Marketing stakeholders, as well as our Agency Network Partner WPP through Open X and Studio X Hub(s).  \n \nThe role: \nSupports, as part of the global StudioX network, in creating the future agenda for StudioX, in anticipation of the future, upgrading it with new capabilities and technologies. \nEnsures the management of SX to support our marketing needs and global vision of simplifying and standardizing and digitizing the work moving through Studio X to deliver exceptional value, effectiveness of marketing work and dollars.   \nFocuses on all aspects of StudioX \u2013 building and leading the OU StudioX operations and the implementation of the OU StudioX agenda, while connecting and integrating it to the global StudioX network.  \nOwns and drives the OU Studio X activities, comprising integration of multiple capabilities, stewardship of ways of working (incl. tools) to deliver the Studio X agenda.   \nAssesses and tracks StudioX performance  \nDefines and operationalizes the capacity of StudioX based on aligned volume of work and OU calendar prioritization to execute key marketing programs for OUs and global charters working closely with key stakeholders especially the OU IMX lead, Marketing Operations & Capabilities team  \nSupports Agency Operations Lead by ensuring all StudioX projects are submitted to Workfront. \nWorks with Marketing Ops and Capabilities on the internal engagement and communication strategy  \nCoordinates with Mkt Platform Services at OU level on key services/SLA and trouble shooting. \nSets and articulates performance expectations with WPP and serve as escalation point to manage through to resolution \n \nOrganisational Impact: \nRemit is global and will often be required to support other OU teams,  \nExecution of global strategy and recommending strategies and plans with direct impact on results \nAs an individual contributor operate with broad latitude in a complex environment, be a subject matter expert within the organization & manage large projects or processes. \nCoaches lower-level professionals in skills, delegates work to them and reviews  \nRepresent the function of marketing procurement internally and externally to support a progressive, modern and dynamic approach to business. \n \nInnovation & Complexity \nResponsible for making improvements of processes, systems or products to optimize performance \nSolve problems by identifying the root cause and modifying solutions applied to similar \nAble to work well across multi functions and as part of a global team \nCompetent and comfortable with data and able to represent this in a way that is clearly understood in the business and drives action \n \nCommunication & Influence \nCommunicates with parties within and outside of own job function to influence and manage performance \nFrequently required to communicate with parties external to the organization  \nRequires ability to communicate with marketers easily  \nWill be required to work with OU leaders and other capability managers to adopt standards and ways of working for the team \n \nBehaviours \nAble to work across functions and teams supporting one TCCC supporting the bigger picture at all times \nAct Like an Owner & own the delivery of results and collaborate well with others to achieve end goals.   \nOpen minded and looking to continuously learn and adapt \nAble to constructively challenge and build trusted relationships  \nPositive mindset, curious, hungry to learn and grow and develop Self & Others. \nEntrepreneurial: Be able to work at pace and manage several projects simultaneously \nAble to manage workload independently \n \nSkills & Experience \nGood understanding of digital and data technologies to enhance production platforms \nInsight into how the production industry works and strong knowledge of the field, players & future trends given work of SX. \nExperience of working closely with marketing teams, partnering to deliver outstanding value driven results \nAble to adhere to clear working processes, scopes of work ensuring perfect delivery  \nAble to understand financial models and translate business requirements into implementation plans.  \nAble to work collaboratively as part of a virtual global team to deliver results and share best practices  \nAbility to use data and apply robust analytics to model various business scenarios and analyze resulting cost, impact, risks, and benefits to inform and recommend business solutions.  \nAble to read, edit and interpret contractual documentation and manage contract performance \nMinimum: 9+ years of work experience in commercial marketing, creative business or procurement or relevant related field.  Knowledge of technical aspects of marketing is highly preferred.  \n \n \nEducation Requirements: \nRequired: Undergraduate degree in a related field \nTravel: Up to 20% globally (mostly regional travel) \n \nSkills:\nContinual Improvement Process; Global Sourcing; Category Management; Analytical Thinking; Sourcing and Procurement; Competitor Analysis; Procurement Procedures; Budget Management; Contracts; Microsoft Office; Sourcing (Inactive); Communication; Buyer Representation; Supplier Relationship Management; Problem Solving; Low Cost Country Sourcing; Marketing Capabilities; Negotiation; Economic Cost Drivers\n\n\nOur Purpose and Growth Culture:\nWe are taking deliberate action to nurture an inclusive culture that is grounded in our company purpose, to refresh the world and make a difference. We act with a growth mindset, take an expansive approach to what\u2019s possible and believe in continuous learning to improve our business and ourselves. We focus on four key behaviours \u2013 curious, empowered, inclusive and agile \u2013 and value how we work as much as what we achieve. We believe that our culture is one of the reasons our company continues to thrive after 130+ years. Visit Our Purpose and Vision to learn more about these behaviours and how you can bring them to life in your next role at Coca-Cola.\nWe are an Equal Opportunity Employer and do not discriminate against any employee or applicant for employment because of race, colour, sex, age, national origin, religion, sexual orientation, gender identity and/or expression, status as a veteran, and basis of disability or any other federal, state or local protected class. When we collect your personal information as part of a job application or offer of employment, we do so in accordance with industry standards and best practices and in compliance with applicable privacy laws.\n \nAPPLY NOW\n \n \n \n \n ",
                " \n \n \n \n \nCOCA-COLA BREAKS SENIOR BRAND MANAGER-AFRICA\nLocation: Johannesburg, Gauteng ZA\nAdditional Locations: Nairobi, Nairobi Area, KEAlgiers, Algiers, DZCairo, Al Qahirah, EGLagos, Lagos, NG\nJob ID: R-95541\nTime Type: Full time\nJob Type: Full-time\nRelocation: No\nPost Date: October 25, 2023\nShare This Job\nCoca-Cola Breaks Senior Brand Manager-Africa\n \nAPPLY NOW\n \nWhat You will Do:\nDevelop short- (1 year) and mid-term (2-3 years) business/brand plans identifying business objectives, strategies, key initiatives and performance measurements by using insights collected from situation assessment, marketplace information, etc. in order to support Africa Operating Unit category and brand growth targets.\nAssess attractive local Africa Operating Unit consumer opportunities that are currently untapped by the Company by leveraging consumer research in order to identify new volume and profit growth areas (e.g., new beverage sub-categories, new packaging opportunities, new merchandise categories, new channels of distribution to sell licensed merchandise).\nProvide direction, leadership and coaching to members of project teams. \nManage Brand Net Revenue, Gross Profit, Direct Marketing Expenditure to deliver Africa Operating Unit brand growth and financial targets.\nDevelop programs and secure required budget in order to execute brand plan.  Where applicable, ensure appropriate implementation of global/regional direction into local execution.\n \nRole Requirements:\nBachelor's degree required, MBA preferred.\n8-10 years of brand management / marketing experience.  Innovation experience a plus (demonstrated ability to lead a concept from idea to shelf).\nCPG Experience a plus\nAbility to manage a Africa Operating Unit brand \u2013 inclusive of key strategies and innovative plans and initiatives \u2013 while motivating/leading, coordinating and working with key internal and external cross-functional partners to deliver on long- (3+ years), mid- and short-term objectives and business plan metrics\nLocation is flexible with Africa Operating Unit\n \nFunctional Skills:\nBrand Equity\nMarketing concepts\nMarketing operating strategies\nCreative concept evaluation\nStrong financial acumen and business analytics\nLeadership and Project management\n \nWhat We Can Do for You:\nYou will be part of the Africa Marketing team where teams are the new heroes and our leaders are inclusive orchestrators. Together, in pursuit of our Company Vision to craft LOVED BRANDS, done SUSTAINABLY, FOR A BETTER SHARED FUTURE, we will:\n\u00b7         Make our CULTURE Code inevitable\n\u00b7         Build winning CAPABILITIES\n\u00b7         Change the DNA of our organization to becoming ADAPTABLE\n \nOur Purpose and Growth Culture:\nWe are taking deliberate action to nurture an inclusive culture that is grounded in our company purpose, to refresh the world and make a difference. We act with a growth mindset, take an expansive approach to what\u2019s possible and believe in continuous learning to improve our business and ourselves. We focus on four key behaviours \u2013 curious, empowered, inclusive and agile \u2013 and value how we work as much as what we achieve. We believe that our culture is one of the reasons our company continues to thrive after 130+ years. Visit Our Purpose and Vision to learn more about these behaviours and how you can bring them to life in your next role at Coca-Cola.\nWe are an Equal Opportunity Employer and do not discriminate against any employee or applicant for employment because of race, colour, sex, age, national origin, religion, sexual orientation, gender identity and/or expression, status as a veteran, and basis of disability or any other federal, state or local protected class. When we collect your personal information as part of a job application or offer of employment, we do so in accordance with industry standards and best practices and in compliance with applicable privacy laws.\n \nAPPLY NOW\n \n \n \n \n ",
                "FRONTLINE MARKETING MANAGER - SOUTH AFRICA\nLocation: Johannesburg, Gauteng ZA\nJob ID: R-95261\nTime Type: Full time\nJob Type: Full-time\nRelocation: No\nPost Date: October 23, 2023\nShare This Job\nFrontline Marketing Manager \u2013 South Africa\n \nAPPLY NOW\n \nWhat You will Do for Us\nFrontline Marketing Manager will be the marketing lead for the respective country/region with the overall responsibility for the local relevance, alignment and implementation of marketing plans. Working closely with Country team, Bottling partners and collaborating across all functions to deliver the business plans as measured by volume, share and profit.\nLead the execution and amplification of marketing plans in the local market as per the brands strategy and operating unit strategy\nProvide nuanced country/regional level input on marketing strategy and plans (e.g. consumer / shopper insights).\nDevelop relationships with key bottlers and ensure alignment and buy-in on market agenda.\nCoordinate full details (calendars, resources, metrics) of local activation with Bottlers.\nIdentify needs for campaign localization or customization as necessary.\nProvide input on media buying (in partnership with Market procurement).\n \nRole Requirement\nBachelor's Degree\n8+ years significant market and leadership experience.\nDirect experience with marketing activation.\nIdeally experience working with TCCC external partners (bottlers and customers).\nExperience working in cross-functional and cross-geographical teams is preferred.\nFMCG experience is an added advantage\n \nFunctional Skills:\nMarketing activation / execution                                \nPOs and experiential marketing                                  \nBusiness / Commercial Acumen                                   \nRelationship management (with INTERNAL & external stakeholders)        \n \nWhat We Can Do for You:\nYou will be part of the Africa team where teams are the new heroes and our leaders are inclusive orchestrators. Together, in pursuit of our Company Vision to craft LOVED BRANDS, done SUSTAINABLY, FOR A BETTER SHARED FUTURE, we will:\nLeverage our BOUNDERLESS NETWORK\nMake our CULTURE Code inevitable\nBuild winning CAPABILITIES\nChange the DNA of our organization to becoming ADAPTABLE\n \nSkills:\nMedia Planning; Influencing; Sponsorships; Local Advertising; Shopper Marketing; Online Marketing; Marketing Activation; Consumer Segmentation; Creative Briefs; Competitive Assessments; Digital Media Strategy; Marketing Strategies; SWOT Analysis; Brand Positioning; Social Media Strategies; Problem Solving; Brand Architecture; Channel Management; Team Management\n\n\nOur Purpose and Growth Culture:\nWe are taking deliberate action to nurture an inclusive culture that is grounded in our company purpose, to refresh the world and make a difference. We act with a growth mindset, take an expansive approach to what\u2019s possible and believe in continuous learning to improve our business and ourselves. We focus on four key behaviours \u2013 curious, empowered, inclusive and agile \u2013 and value how we work as much as what we achieve. We believe that our culture is one of the reasons our company continues to thrive after 130+ years. Visit Our Purpose and Vision to learn more about these behaviours and how you can bring them to life in your next role at Coca-Cola.\nWe are an Equal Opportunity Employer and do not discriminate against any employee or applicant for employment because of race, colour, sex, age, national origin, religion, sexual orientation, gender identity and/or expression, status as a veteran, and basis of disability or any other federal, state or local protected class. When we collect your personal information as part of a job application or offer of employment, we do so in accordance with industry standards and best practices and in compliance with applicable privacy laws.\n \nAPPLY NOW"
